  "chunks": [
    {
      "chunk_type": "isnad",
      "arabic_text": "الْحُسَيْنُ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ وَغَيْرُهُ عَنْ جَعْفَرِ بْنِ مُحَمَّدٍ عَنْ عَلِيِّ بْنِ الْعَبَّاسِ بْنِ عَامِرٍ عَنْ مُوسَى بْنِ هِلَالٍ الْكِنْدِيِّ عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عَطَاءٍ عَنْ أَبِي جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ قَالَ",
      "translations": {
        "en": "Al-Ḥusayn ibn Muḥammad and another, from Jaʿfar ibn Muḥammad, from ʿAlī ibn al-ʿAbbās ibn ʿĀmir, from Mūsā ibn Hilāl al-Kindī, from ʿAbdullāh ibn ʿAṭāʾ, from Abī Jaʿfar عليه السلام, who said:"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "opening",
      "arabic_text": "قُلْتُ لَهُ إِنَّ شِيعَتَكَ بِالْعِرَاقِ كَثِيرَةٌ وَاللَّهِ مَا فِي أَهْلِ بَيْتِكَ مِثْلُكَ فَكَيْفَ لَا تَخْرُجُ",
      "translations": {
        "en": "I said to him: “Indeed, your Shiʿah in al-ʿIrāq are many. By Allah, there is none like you among your Ahl al-Bayt, so how is it that you do not rise?”"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "body",
      "arabic_text": "قَالَ فَقَالَ يَا عَبْدَ اللَّهِ بْنَ عَطَاءٍ قَدْ أَخَذْتَ تَفْرُشُ أُذُنَيْكَ لِلنَّوْكَى إِي وَاللَّهِ مَا أَنَا بِصَاحِبِكُمْ",
      "translations": {
        "en": "He said: “O ʿAbdullāh ibn ʿAṭāʾ, you have begun spreading your ears for the foolish. Yes, by Allah, I am not your Sahib.”"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "body",
      "arabic_text": "قَالَ قُلْتُ لَهُ فَمَنْ صَاحِبُنَا قَالَ انْظُرُوا مَنْ عَمِيَ عَلَى النَّاسِ وِلَادَتُهُ فَذَاكَ صَاحِبُكُمْ",
      "translations": {
        "en": "He said: I said to him, “Then who is our Sahib?” He said: “Look to the one whose birth is hidden from the people; that one is your Sahib.”"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "closing",
      "arabic_text": "إِنَّهُ لَيْسَ مِنَّا أَحَدٌ يُشَارُ إِلَيْهِ بِالْإِصْبَعِ وَيُمْضَغُ بِالْأَلْسُنِ إِلَّا مَاتَ غَيْظًا أَوْ رَغِمَ أَنْفُهُ",
      "translations": {
        "en": "Indeed, there is no one from us who is pointed at by fingers and chewed by tongues except that he dies in anger or his nose is rubbed in humiliation.”
      }
    }
  ],
  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "summary": "This hadith reports that Abū Jaʿfar عليه السلام rejected the assumption that he would be the openly rising Qa'im, despite the large number of Shiʿah in al-ʿIrāq. He identifies the true Sahib as the one whose birth will be hidden from the people, and states that any one of the Ahl al-Bayt who becomes publicly singled out and widely discussed will meet a frustrated end.",
      "seo_question": "Who is the Sahib or Qa'im described by Abū Jaʿfar عليه السلام in this hadith from al-Kāfī?",
      "key_terms": {
        "شِيعَتَكَ": "your followers and adherents",
        "أَهْلِ بَيْتِكَ": "your household, the Ahl al-Bayt",
        "تَخْرُجُ": "to rise or come out against authority",
        "صَاحِبِكُمْ": "your master, referring here to the awaited Qa'im",
        "عَمِيَ": "was concealed or obscured",
        "وِلَادَتُهُ": "his birth",
        "يُشَارُ إِلَيْهِ بِالْإِصْبَعِ": "he is pointed out publicly and singled out",
        "يُمْضَغُ بِالْأَلْسُنِ": "he is spoken about repeatedly by people's tongues"
      }
    }
  },
